    public abstract class AbstractShellCommand

      • parseArguments

        protected List<String> parseArguments(String arguments,
                                      boolean escaping)
        Parses command's arguments and escapes appropriate ones if requested. Escaped characters can be '"' and '\'.If escaping is enabled then all word within quotes are parsed as single argument.
        Parameters:
        arguments - string which will be parsed
        escaping - if true escaping is enabled
        Returns:
        parsed arguments
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if escaping is enabled and some quotes aren't closed

      • checkExpectedArguments

        protected boolean checkExpectedArguments(Environment env,
                                         List<String> args,
                                         int minCount,
                                         int maxCount)
        Checks if argument count is valid. If it's not appropriate message is printed.
        Parameters:
        env - reference to the environment in which command is called
        args - arguments to check
        minCount - minimum number of arguments
        maxCount - maximum number of arguments
        Returns:
        true if argument count is valid, else false
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if minimum count is greater than max count
